<p><b>What's the hardest math problem on earth?</b> 1. Riemann Hypothesis. The Riemann Hypothesis, proposed by Bernhard Riemann in 1859, is a central problem in number theory, and discusses the distribution of prime numbers. The hypothesis focuses on the zeros of the Riemann zeta function.</p>
